DIRECTIONS\
		\uc0\u8232 Step 1.   Whisk lime juice, cilantro, garlic salt, and black pepper together in a large glass or ceramic bowl. Add chicken; toss to evenly coat. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator, 30 minutes to overnight.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 2.   Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 3.   Remove chicken from marinade and shake off excess. Discard remaining marinade.\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
		\uc0\u8232 Step 4.  Cook chicken on the preheated grill, turning occasionally, until no longer pink at the bone and juices run clear, about 30 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 \
